cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it focuses on the design of specialized hardware accelerators for convolutional neural networks. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it deals with feature maps in CNNs, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the optimization of ML models for deployment on embedded and mobile systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the compression of feature maps in neural networks.
